ive had this game since the first day of alpha and i can confidentally say that nothing comes close to arma 3 in potential except maybe arma 2 and minecraft its a fantastic sandbox military simulator where you can do anything you could imagine no matter how dumb its a game where content is developed by the community for the community there are no set game modes or official servers there aren even any official game modes you can even download on their website its a completely player created game feel like invading either the islands of altis and stratis one minute and then roleplaying as a drug dealer the next sure why not its completely possible in arma 3 pros  almost limitless potential  close to an unlimited number of gamemodes created by the community  hundreds of community made campaigns and mods both avaliable on the workshop and on armaholic the goto place for arma mods  massive maps with none of those dumb loading screens every other game with maps on these scales seem to have stratis is 1520km2 altis is 270km2  large maps load very well and are very stable  the ability to have infantry armor naval and air battles at the exact same time on a much larger scale than you could imagine in another game such as battlefield  a wide variety of weapons vehicles and clothing cons  vehicles tend to explode a bit easier than they should  possibility of desync occuring on servers if they are overloaded  hit markers and boxes can be a bit buggy and glitchy  possibility of some pretty big lag adding too many itemsvehiclesaiplayers to the games already massive maps as you can see the pros easily outweight the cons this game is fantastic even if you dont want to pay the full price for it it goes on sale often enough and i promise you wont regret it 910
