highly recommended great graphics epic gameplay endless options for multiplayer modes though cti and tdm are my favorite i fell in love with this game it simply rocks though one should be aware this is nothing like the bf series etc you either love or hate arma as simple as that if you like games like aa3 and red orchestra etc chances are you will absolutley love arma all in all give it a try if its on a steam sale or if once of your friends already got it
recommended
the arma series has always been more of a simulator than a video game as such it is not easy to get into there are tons of keybinds the movement systems feels wonky due to being so tied to the animation system and confrontations seem more a test of patience rather than reflex engagements usually at 100 meters or more it also doesnt help that the ai can be incredibly incredibly stupid despite this the series has garnered a strong following that has created a community of serious players that is hard to find anywhere else now comes arma 3 arma 3 is not a fundamentally different game but the developers have learned from the past and they have given this iteration a sense of polish that makes it refreshing to this jaded arma fan and very enticing to those curious about the series but otherwise intimidated by arma 2 and 1 first off arma 3 looks stunning the island is modeled after a real mediterranean island and it shows there is a strong sense of authenticity as you walk run fly and fight through the landscape it is worth plopping down a unit in the editor and just walking around absorbing the sights the vastly improved lighting engine really adds to the entire experience lighthouses illuminate the world convincingly and fires cast an impressive glow what makes the game feel so much better is the improved controls no longer do you move like a drunken mudcrab as one of my friends so succinctly said indeed the past games always made movement a struggle with its reverse mouse acceleration clumsy walking and running and strange deadzonefree aim mechanic which a lot of arma fans swear by but i personally detest now with arma3 the mouse is no longer hampered by that pesky reverse acceleration movement is more fluid with some nice little touches such as tactical pace and it introduces a fantastic modifier system that lets you pop up and down left and right for each stance its a simple addition but adds so much to the combat especially in a world where no cover is a perfect chest high wall the game also comes with a powerful editor while it is extremely daunting even the most passing user can make some interesting scenarios and for those who really want to learn there are tools that will let you decompile other peoples missions to see how they do things its very much worth exploring especially if you enjoy thinking of tactical what if situations what is most impressive is that my experiences with arma 3 so far have only been in alpha despite this it runs and plays great and things can only get better from here already with the second update performance and stability has increased tremendously as an alpha i am already recommending this game highly honestly if you are tired of the constant closed quarter combat corridor shooters like call of duty and if battlefield 3 just doesnt seem real enough for you check out arma 3 it just might scratch that itch of yours
