recommended
as you can see from this review i have almost 500 hours in the game so if youre looking for someone who knows it trust me arma 3 is a military simulator which means that you arent getting the constant grinding freeforall match ups you find in fps games like call of duty or battlefield it also doesnt get much more realistic than this but in terms of the actual game there are a plethora of things to do there are altis life rpg servers which allow you to play the way you want within certain constraints of course there are wasteland servers as well which is essentially a giant battlefield for you to play in also if you get a group of people you can run some pretty awesome missions not to mention have a blast with the zeus mode which allows a player to become a game master and run a mission dynamically yes there are bugs driving full force with a truck into a tank probably wouldnt cause it to blow up for example rocks walls and even chickenwire fences can disable plenty of vehicles and sometimes the actual mechanics are pretty slow but the major bugs that you find are usually because of some faulty coding in a server you play on such as dropping a truck from a helicopter only to have it disappear the next instant or fling back up and blow you out of the sky regardless of these the actual content of arma 3 is massive and the situations you can create get to be incredibly intense the $5999 price tag on this game shouldnt stop you from buying it because it is worth every penny if you want to find some examples of people who play this game and have a great time you can find a ton of videos on youtube that may help you in your decision to buy it lastly i mentioned before that this is not a call of duty or battlefield game they are all there own and you may think that this game is too slowpaced if you are looking for that runandgun format of a game but whileplaying this game you find yourself in many different situations whether it be sneaking up to a compound while trying to avoid any contact laserdesignating a target for airsupport to pulverize or peaking around and pieing corners in a cqb scenario you will find thousands of these unique situations which make this game worthwhile to nearly every fan of fpss and milsims alike
