carrying on from the genredefining milsim that was arma 2 arma 3 is a rock solid sequel that lives up to the expectations in place for the arma series even managing to go a bit beyond in certain aspects as a great fan of arma 2 i love arma 3 and the improvements bi have managed to implement into the game as well as showing off nearfuture battlefield tech in the game to help accurately represent the games time period bi have also managed to develop great maps interesting gamemodes wasteland for online play and still manage to maintain and improve upon the fun level of realism that made arma 2 so popular with milsim players the modding scene is also very active with mods such as ace and acre out there for added realism and more serious milsim players which allows the game to be expanded upon a lot be warned however the game isnt shy on performance and requires a decent rig to run properly even on midrange settings my only major whine about the game itself is the developers choice to release the campaign in a series of episodes dripfeeding us content and missions but as each episode is released this negative becomes less and less of a factor im giving arma 3 a 910 and deffinitely recommend this game
