arma 3 takes me back to the days of deltaforce long time ago it being a thoroughly enjoyable tactical military shooter albeit with its own special glitches and graphics fails the interface may seem somewhat clunky at first but you soon overcome that and although the game has many controls they quickly become familiar and are relatively intuitive the scales and graphics on arma are pretty impressive although as in many games the graphics are less impressive up close less the textures and more the number and complexity of objects however with a game of this size if each house was packed with objects you can bet the frames are going to take a massive hit what bohemia have done is find a reasonable balance with this generally the environment looks great there are some questionable physics interactions which can make for some strange happenings although that is part of the charm with arma if you want a military sim that generally plays pretty well with a decent amount of guns and vehicles to mess about in then this is well worth it whilst not quite as slick as some games built on newer game engines arma does hold up pretty well
