i was really hopeful about arma as it is it was pretty lame maybe itd be better if i had a super fast computer and everyone had the fastest internet known to mankind it is almost as realistic as warthunder but jumpy jagged and with laggy multiplayer some say the controls are confusing but i dont agree the controls are a little different but you get used to them fairly quickly some of the confusion comes from putting more than one action with the same button switching based on whether it is a tap or a hold i referenced the controls menu a bunch but there are numerous tutorials guides training scenarios and other practice available right in the game i really appreciate how realistic it is in that there are no markers for the enemy and it only takes a couple of hits to kill you unfortunately it always takes at least 4 bullets to kill an enemy unless you hit the face the helmet will not do you must hit the face or neck this is actually pretty hard to do when you are at distances of 100m which you usually are engaging at those distances  50m and when they shoot more accurately than you because you have been walkingrunning everywhere and thus have less fatigue avoid ever sprinting even though the map is bigger than any map in any other game youve ever played in just be patient and take 24 minutes to walk to the next battle if you run youll just die tired i went into a multiplayer game and saw helicopters flying around in crazy upside down positions crashing and falling to the ground perhaps a contributing factor was the fact that it was a 70 person game when i joined i saw in the chat room that players were complaining about the lag as i quickly downloaded a 34 mb setting file from the server obviously my joining the game clogged their upstream pipe this happened a couple times in the game as new players joined lag spiked perhaps a fix of this could be a download mirror used for all servers or something to save on server bandwidth this game made me laugh at how unpolished it was at several points mostly this was for multiplayer lag jumps but it was funny when i tried my first multiplayer mission and my trooper who was not the squad leader would not stop calling out orders to everyone every 10 seconds i tried figuring out why i was issuing all these commands but it happened without my pressing buttons or anything close to the squad command buttons it was also funny because the ingame voice chat toggle button defaults to [caps lock] so when i returned to typing out messages they were shouting half the time oops i couldnt figure out how to stop ordering everyone to regroup with me nor could i find the enemy it was a coop mission so i decided to try something else in my second multiplayer game i was starting to get the hang of it i died plenty at first sure but there was always a nice helicopter pilot ready to take us to the battlefield when i respawned im really glad i didnt have to walk all that way because if i did once would have been enough for me to quit i was starting to get the hang of it and even a few kills someone finally got me while from a higher building and i was returning to the battlefield in a helicopter i started typing to my teammates while riding in the heli and even though i was typing a message when i used spacebar during the message it caused me to jump out of the helicopter without a parachute i died before i could finish typing out my question but in a way it answered a different one i decided to stop playing multiplayer and try the campaign in the first mission it was funny to have an enemy blazing away full tilt at my essential npc partner and for him to not even notice the enemy was there walking on by i would have preferred my ai teammate to actually engage the enemy but im sure walking up and shoulder checking him as he walked by was pretty effective in the same mission i snuck up on a machine gunner in the same first mission and wanted to see what the action button would do when i got close it turns out instead of knifing him or doing some other crazycool cqb maneuver i pulled out my medical kit and started bandaging him while he turned his mg on my face and opened up in the second mission i wasnt able to progress because one member of my squad spotted an mrap that he really wanted me to destroy even when our mission didnt call for it the rest of our squad was fine to go to the rendezvous point but that npc squad member kept yelling for us to take out the group of enemies by it the squad leader kept yelling for him to return to formation and i just kept walking through the forest for a while hoping that hed return at the next script line for the story he didnt i ended up going back to the last autosave and taking out the rest of them by myself after 20 tries without backup i was a little glad i did because when allies engage the enemy they die as fast as the enemy does which is as fast as you do which is quick i never neded up finishing that mission because even when i knew generally where the enemy was coming from i couldnt see them to shoot them but they sure could see and shoot me through all the leaves and bushes in the forest i died over and over im sure it was a bit like nam and just as fun so i decided to uninstall if it werent for that the campaign at least has great production value on par with call of duty the voice acting scripting of scenes and music all are top notch it is ready for oculus ir and maybe id enjoy it more if i had a computer that wasnt at least 6 years old i am usually a simulation enthusiast loving realism even over gameplay hey i like warthunder where you also have a hard time identifying who is an enemy and you die in 12 hits however this was just not very enjoyable arma is like fighting on 3 or 4 battlefield 3 maps at once with 100 players that sounds fun and it could be as it is however it tries to do entirely too much for my computer it ends up being a laggy frustrating mess itd be fun at a convention on a lan with computers with monster video cards because the draw distance is intense but i was frustrated not having fun and ready to uninstall after just a few hours
